<title>JAPAN: Nippon Oil shuts Muroran topper for maintenance.</title>
<headline>Nippon Oil shuts Muroran topper for maintenance.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nippon Oil Co Ltd said on Friday it had closed its 170,000 barrel-per-day (bpd) crude distillation unit (CDU) at the Muroran refinery on Japan's northern island of Hokkaido for regular maintenance checks.</p>
<p>The topper is scheduled to resume operations on June 30, a Nippon Oil spokesman said.</p>
<p>Major refining facilities to be affected by the turnaround are as follows:</p>
<p>Facility			 Capacity		    Date</p>
<p>			     (barrels per day)</p>
<p>Topper			   170,000		 May 23 - June 30</p>
<p>Fluid catalytic</p>
<p> cracker			  23,000		 May 20 - July 2</p>
<p>Residue desulphuriser	 12,500		 May 18 - July 2</p>
<p>Hydrocracker		    40,000		 May 20 - July 2</p>
<p>--Tokyo Energy Desk +81-3-3432-8837</p>
